<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Coscinodiscophyceae" family="Aulacoseiraceae" genus="Aulacoseira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aulacoseira islandica" order="Aulacoseirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="islandica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Aulacoseira islandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most often occurring as planktonic or tychoplanktonic taxon in water bodies of different types in high latitude or high altitude oligotrophic to mesotrophic large waters (
<bibRefCitation author="Houk, V" journalOrPublisher="Diatom Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B60" refString="Houk, V, Klee, R, Tanaka, H, 2010. Atlas of freshwater centric diatoms with a brief key and descriptions, Part III. Stephanodiscaceae A. Cyclotella, Tertiarius, Discostella Fottea 10 (Suppl.): 1-498." title="Atlas of freshwater centric diatoms with a brief key and descriptions, Part III. Stephanodiscaceae A. Cyclotella, Tertiarius, Discostella Fottea 10 (Suppl.): 1 - 498." year="2010">Houk et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
; Stoermer and Julius 2013; 
<bibRefCitation author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Filigran, Yaroslavl" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B45" refString="Genkal, SI, Kulikovskiy, MS, Kuznetsova, IV, 2020. Modern freshwater centric diatom algae in Russia [Sovremennye presnovodnye centricheskie diatomovye vodorosli Rossii]. Filigran, Yaroslavl" title="Modern freshwater centric diatom algae in Russia [Sovremennye presnovodnye centricheskie diatomovye vodorosli Rossii]." year="2020">Genkal et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Sometimes this species may even cause a spring bloom (Stoermer and Julius 2013).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
This species was observed in all sampling sites and is the first confirmed record for the whole basin of the Southern Bug River (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Species composition of centric diatoms at the investigated sites near Mykolaiv city in the Southern Bug River in the year 2017 (2013 added for station 2)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" tableUuid="DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677">1</tableCitation>
). In the mid-1930s 
<bibRefCitation author="Swirenko, DO" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fuer Hydrobiologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="593 - 770" refId="B121" refString="Swirenko, DO, 1941. Die botanischen Ergebnisse der Sued-Bugishen Hydrobiologischen Expedition. Archiv fuer Hydrobiologie 6 (4): 593 - 770" title="Die botanischen Ergebnisse der Sued-Bugishen Hydrobiologischen Expedition." volume="6" year="1941">Swirenko (1941)</bibRefCitation>
found this species as 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Coscinodiscophyceae" family="Melosiraceae" genus="Melosira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Melosira islandica subsp. var. var. helvetica" order="Melosirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="islandica" subSpecies="var." variety="helvetica">Melosira islandica var. helvetica</taxonomicName>
O. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
in the lower part of the River starting from Mygea rapids and some other lower stations along the River bed to the mouth (
<bibRefCitation author="Swirenko, DO" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fuer Hydrobiologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="593 - 770" refId="B121" refString="Swirenko, DO, 1941. Die botanischen Ergebnisse der Sued-Bugishen Hydrobiologischen Expedition. Archiv fuer Hydrobiologie 6 (4): 593 - 770" title="Die botanischen Ergebnisse der Sued-Bugishen Hydrobiologischen Expedition." volume="6" year="1941">Swirenko 1941</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Coscinodiscophyceae" family="Aulacoseiraceae" genus="Aulacoseira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aulacoseira islandica" order="Aulacoseirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="islandica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Aulacoseira islandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the Dnipro River basin and its reservoirs (
<bibRefCitation author="Tsarenko, PM" journalOrPublisher="Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B127" refString="Tsarenko, PM, Wasser, SP, Nevo, E, 2009. Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A.R.A. Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" title="Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A. R. A." year="2009">Tsarenko et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
It is also a common species for Europe (Bulgaria, Iran, Finland, Germany, Lithuania, Romania, Russia, Sweden, Ukraine), Asia (Georgia, Russia, Turkmenistan), North America (Canada, Greenland, USA); Barents, Bering and White Seas (
<bibRefCitation author="Tsarenko, PM" journalOrPublisher="Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B127" refString="Tsarenko, PM, Wasser, SP, Nevo, E, 2009. Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A.R.A. Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" title="Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A. R. A." year="2009">Tsarenko et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
